    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Top and tail the<strong> aubergine<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>and slice, lengthways into 8 <span class=\"text-danger\">[16]</span> thin wedges, then add them to a baking tray (or two!) with the<strong> cherry tomatoes</strong>,<strong> harissa paste </strong>(can’t handle the heat? Go easy!), a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Mix everything together and put the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> in the oven for 20-25 min or until tender – these are your <strong>roasted aubergine wedges & tomatoes</strong></p>",
